{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 20:47:39.577613", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Method\\n- Verified end-to-end reachability across hosts, servers, and infrastructure.\\n- Measured HTTP performance from two user hosts to the named web services and the load balancer.\\n- Inspected interface and queuing/traffic control (tc) configuration on servers and the server access router.\\n- Correlated latency and timing results with device configurations.\\n\\nHigh-Level Health Summary\\n- IP reachability: Healthy. All tested pairs show 0% packet loss, OSPF-connected subnets are reachable.\\n- DNS: Healthy. Name lookup times generally <100 ms and typically single-digit milliseconds.\\n- Load balancer (web99.local): Healthy and consistent. TTFB ~0.24–0.33 s, total ~1.0–1.1 s across tests.\\n- Front-end web servers (web0.local, web2.local, web3.local): Reachable; HTTP performance variable but generally within 1.0–2.1 s total per curl with small DNS/connect phases.\\n\\nDetected Anomaly\\n- web1.local (web_server_1) exhibits consistently elevated latency and reduced network performance compared to peer web servers.\\n  - Ping RTTs from multiple hosts to 10.200.0.4 average ~22–27 ms, versus low single-digit milliseconds to other web servers under similar paths.\\n  - HTTP tests to web1.local show higher and more variable TTFB/total times (e.g., several runs with TTFB ~1.2–1.7 s and total up to ~4 s), worse than peers.\\n\\nLocalization of Fault\\n- The anomaly localizes to web_server_1’s network interface, not the server access router or core/distribution layers:\\n  - web_server_1 (eth0) tc configuration:\\n    - qdisc netem 1: root … delay 20ms\\n    - qdisc tbf 10: parent 1:1 rate 1Mbit burst 500Kb\\n    - tc -s shows “overlimits 1156” on the TBF, indicating active rate limiting.\\n  - Other web servers (web_server_0/2/3) have default fq_codel qdisc with no artificial delay or rate limit.\\n  - Server access router (interfaces eth1–eth7) uses default fq_codel; no netem/tbf applied there.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Artificial traffic shaping on web_server_1 eth0:\\n  - A netem delay of 20 ms adds ~20 ms one-way (≈ 20–25 ms observed RTTs are consistent with only egress delayed on the reply path).\\n  - A TBF limiting egress to 1 Mbit/s substantially reduces throughput and can increase application perceived latency under load (confirmed by overlimits counters).\\n- This configuration is unique to web_server_1 among the front-end servers and explains its degraded and variable performance.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Direct access to web1.local is adversely affected by added latency and bandwidth constriction.\\n- Other front-end web servers (web0/2/3) and the load balancer (web99.local) do not show this network-level impairment.\\n- Backend load-balanced service via web99.local appears normal and consistent, suggesting no broader routing or server-access-router issue.\\n\\nSupporting Evidence\\n- Reachability tests: 0% loss; RTTs to web_server_1 significantly higher than to other web servers.\\n- curl timings:\\n  - web99.local: starttransfer ~0.24–0.33 s; total ~1.0–1.1 s.\\n  - web1.local: starttransfer often ~1.2 s (one run ~0.35 s), total up to ~4.3 s; generally poorer than peers.\\n- tc on web_server_1 eth0:\\n  - netem delay 20ms and TBF 1Mbit configured; tc -s shows active rate limiting (overlimits).\\n- tc elsewhere:\\n  - web_server_0/2/3: default fq_codel only; no delay/rate shaping.\\n  - server_access_router all ports: default fq_codel only; no shaping.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Anomaly exists and is confirmed: degraded latency and performance specifically to web1.local.\\n- Fault localized to web_server_1 network interface configuration.\\n- Root cause identified: tc netem (20 ms delay) and tbf (1 Mbit/s) applied on web_server_1 eth0, causing added latency and bandwidth restriction., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='f69535a5-0db5-4a84-87bd-9cf2245b3da0'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
